** About Us **

** The Power to Respond and Be Heard **

For 40 years, Zetron (a Codan company) has delivered interoperable command &
control systems.

Across multiple industries and international markets. Zetron is headquartered
in Redmond, WA, USA, with centres of engineering excellence in Victoria, BC,
Canada, and Brisbane, QLD, Australia & United Kingdom. Zetron currently has
over 40,000 console positions, hundreds of established partners and value-
added resellers, and coverage in more than 100 countries and 7 continents.
Zetron is an established global leader in connecting communications centres
with field operations, personnel, and constituents. Our products make a real
difference, they get police, fire and ambulance services to the scene of an
incident, and they assist with keeping the power on, the trains running, and
airports operating. Our customers rely on our systems to be to be available
every minute of every day to help keep their staff and the public safe.

We'd love your help. And we'll support you all the way.

Discover us at Mission Critical Communications Solutions - Zetron

** What Will You Be Doing? **

The role of DevOps Engineer will be responsible for contributing to the
success of our cutting-edge projects through collaboration and team engagement
with all internal and external stakeholders to design, implement, and maintain
infrastructure solutions.

** As a key member of the team, you will: **

  * Automate deployment, monitoring, and management processes to ensure efficient and reliable systems operation. 
  * Implement and manage CI/CD pipelines for software delivery. 
  * Troubleshoot and resolve infrastructure and pipeline issues, ensuring high availability and 
  * performance. 
  * Collaborate with developers to optimise applications for performance and scalability. 
  * Stay up to date with industry best practices and emerging technologies. 

** Core essential Skills will include, but not be limited to: **

  * Strong knowledge of Vertulization platforms 
  * Solid understanding of networking concepts and security best practices (SecOps). 
  * Proven expertise in CI/CD tools 
  * Hands-on experience with configuration management tools. 
  * Experience with monitoring and logging tools 
  * Knowledge of cloud platforms 
  * Familiarity with version control systems 

** About You **

We are looking for a passionate and experienced DevOps Engineer to complement
our small but growing and engaged DevOps team. Your aligned technical
experience will be complemented by high level organisational, communication
and interpersonal skills that will facilitate positive business outcomes for
all internal and external stakeholders. Aligned qualifications in Computer
Science, Information Technology or another related field would be highly
beneficial.

  
  

** Benefits and Culture **

Located in Stafford, Queensland, our culture is supportive and collaborative.
You will be part of a multidisciplinary team where we share our ideas and
innovation is strongly encouraged. We are looking for someone with genuine
passion and a can-do attitude for what they do. Zetron embodies the values of
those who work here, embraces diversity, and offers a comfortable and casual
atmosphere where people work hard and feel a part of the organisation. At
Zetron we not only create and stand behind products that help save lives, but
our employees are also offered a competitive compensation and benefits
package, including:

  * Career development program 
  * Flexible working hours 
  * Employee Assistance Program 
  * Short term incentive program 
  * Onsite parking 

